1. Create an array of all the stalls and their respective items.
2. Create another array to store the count of each item sold by each stall.
3. Iterate through the array of stalls and their items, and for each item, increment the count of the stalls selling that item.
4. Sort the array of items by the count of stalls selling them in descending order.
5. Return the top N items, where N is the number of stalls in the market.

